(288, 1, '2025-08-29 10:34:06', '2025-08-29 09:32:50', ' ', '', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '288', '', '', '2025-08-29 10:34:06', '2025-08-29 09:34:06', '', 0, 'https://www.astemes.com/staging/2025/288/', 3, 'nav_menu_item', '', 0),
(289, 1, '2025-08-29 10:32:50', '2025-08-29 09:32:50', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We have developed and maintain open source projects available at the <a href=\"https://github.com/astemes\">Astemes GitHub site</a>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:media-text {\"mediaId\":285,\"mediaLink\":\"https://www.astemes.com/staging/?attachment_id=285\",\"mediaType\":\"image\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-media-text is-stacked-on-mobile\"><figure class=\"wp-block-media-text__media\"><img src=\"https://www.astemes.com/staging/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/LUnit.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-285 size-full\"/></figure><div class=\"wp-block-media-text__content\"><!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">LUnit Unit Testing Framework</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://lunit.astemes.com/\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://lunit.astemes.com/\">LUnit</a> has become one of the leading unit testing frameworks in the LabVIEW community. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Sam Taggart wrote a great <a href=\"https://blog.sasworkshops.com/lunit/\">blog post on LUnit</a> and there are multiple presentations available <a href=\"https://www.astemes.com/staging/presentations/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"280\">here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div></div>\n<!-- /wp:media-text -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">LMock</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":286,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.astemes.com/staging/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/image-1024x264.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-286\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://lmock.astemes.com/\">LMock</a> is a mocking framework which automates test double generation and provides a very expressive API for writing mock-based unit tests.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">CSV Report Plugin for NI TestStand</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":287,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.astemes.com/staging/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/excel-1024x291.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-287\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/astemes/astemes-csv-report-teststand-plugin\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://github.com/astemes/astemes-csv-report-teststand-plugin\">This</a> is a neat little reporting plugin for NI TestStand which generates a csv based report, which can easily be worked with in e.g. Excel. This conveniently simplifies result analysis, as no markdown parsing or special reader is necessary. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">LUnit Add-Ons</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Because LUnit is written using a plugin based design, it is possible to extend the toolkit with custom addons. Below is a list of current addons maintained by Astemes.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>LUnit CLI</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Type / to add a hidden block\"} -->\n<p>The <a href=\"https://github.com/astemes/astemes-lunit-cli\">LUnit Command Line Interface (CLI)</a> is used for running LUnit in a Continuous Integration workflow. It is built with LabVIEW native CLI and is available on <a href=\"https://www.vipm.io/package/astemes_lib_lunit_cli/\">VIPM</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>LUnit Parameterized Add-On</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Type / to add a hidden block\"} -->\n<p>This <a href=\"https://github.com/astemes/astemes-lunit-parameterized-test\">add-on</a> makes it simple to write parameterized unit tests, meaning that each test method may be executed for each parameter in a list. The add-on is also available on <a href=\"https://www.vipm.io/package/astemes_lib_lunit_parameterized_add_on/\">VIPM</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>LUnit Test Inheritance Add-On</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Type / to add a hidden block\"} -->\n<p>The first release of LUnit had the concept of test inheritance as a built in feature. As the toolkit has evolved this has been extracted into a <a href=\"https://github.com/Astemes/astemes-lunit-test-inheritance/\">separate add-on</a>, as it is not a central feature to the tool. The addon is however still maintained and available on <a href=\"https://www.vipm.io/package/astemes_lib_lunit_test_inheritance_add_on/\">VIPM</a>. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>LUnit Global Fixture Add-On</summary><!-- wp:paragraph {\"placeholder\":\"Type / to add a hidden block\"} -->\n<p>This <a href=\"https://github.com/Astemes/astemes-lunit-global-fixture\">add-on</a> was developed as a result of a feature request on LUnit. Instead of building in the concept of global fixtures into the toolkit, the feature was released as an add-on and is available on <a href=\"https://www.vipm.io/package/astemes_lib_lunit_global_fixture_add_on/\">VIPM</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Triarc Framework</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Astemes <a href=\"https://github.com/astemes/astemes-triarc-framework\">Test Rig Architecture (Triarc) framework</a> is a very powerful application framework for LabVIEW. It allows you to spawn parallell processes and manages the lifecycle of these processes, as well as messaging between them. Documentation is available <a href=\"https://astemes.github.io/astemes-triarc-framework/\">here</a> and the latest release is published on <a href=\"https://github.com/astemes/astemes-triarc-framework/releases\">GitHub</a>. There is also a separate <a href=\"https://github.com/astemes/astemes-triarc-debugger\">debugger</a> which allows for tracing messages and broadcasts made by each process as they execute. Examples are available <a href=\"https://github.com/astemes/astemes-triarc-examples\">here</a>, which demonstrates the features as compared to other popular frameworks.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Open Source', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '284-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-08-29 10:32:50', '2025-08-29 09:32:50', '', 284, 'https://www.astemes.com/staging/?p=289', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(291, 1, '2025-08-29 10:36:48', '2025-08-29 09:36:48', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On this page you find a catalog of presentations we have given, some available on YouTube. If you would like to arrange a presentation of workshop for your team, please get in touch.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>Building Our Own Tools - The LabVIEW Experiment Podcast</summary><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>While technically not a presentation, we had a great discussion on the <a href=\"https://www.thelabviewexperiment.com/\">LabVIEW Experiment podcast</a>. The episode is available <a href=\"https://open.spotify.com/episode/1f6sazicEYPXuwtNtDP2yQ?si=787c45da9c754f13\">here</a>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>Parameterized Unit Tests - NordLUG 2024</summary><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The <a href=\"https://forums.ni.com/t5/NORDLUG-Nordic-LabVIEW-User/bd-p/nordlugforum-board\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://forums.ni.com/t5/NORDLUG-Nordic-LabVIEW-User/bd-p/nordlugforum-board\">Nordic LabVIEW User Group</a> is a community led forum for LabVIEW developers to connect and discuss various topics. I gave a presentation during the first NordLUG meeting in 2024, where I introduce a toolkit for writing parameterized unit tests. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/YYQr5CSCF9M?si=yY74Lv99IFC8slCd\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/YYQr5CSCF9M?si=yY74Lv99IFC8slCd\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>Refactoring - CNRood Reconnect Helsinki 2024</summary><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During this presentation we discuss refactoring, what it is, why it is needed, and how it can be applied in a LabVIEW environment. We also discuss how we can use testing to protect the code from changing during the refactoring, and tips were shared for tooling on the topic.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This presentation was not recorded, please get in touch if you are interested in the content. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>Unit Testing Workshop - Stuttgart</summary><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We held a half-day long Unit Testing workshop, together with Sam Taggart of <a href=\"https://www.sasworkshops.com/\">SAS Workshops</a> in connection with GDevCon in Stuttgart. The session was well attended and we had some very insightful discussions. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is no recording available. If you are interested in the topics we are happy to arrange similar events, either online, in-person, or as a hybrid.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>Test Driving a Driver - GDevCon #5 Stuttgart</summary><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This was not technically a presentation, but followed the huddle format introduced at GDevCon #5. During the time slot we developed a low level hardware driver for an I2C controlled IO expander IC using test driven development and mocks. We managed to write the driver in the 45 minute session, by always doing the test first. At the end of the session we connected a breadboard with the IC on it and were able to blink some LEDs using the code we developed during the session.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This huddle session was not recorded, please get in touch if you are interested in the content. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I later made the content into an exercise with step by step instructions. The exercise is freely available <a href=\"https://github.com/astemes/astemes-mocking-exercise\" data-type=\"link\" data-id=\"https://github.com/astemes/astemes-mocking-exercise\">here</a> for anyone interested.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>LUnit Demonstration - TMiLV</summary><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I was invited to give a demonstration of LUnit by the excellent This Month in LabVIEW (TMiLV) YouTube channel. This demonstration walks through the basics of LUnit.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/Cxb1FUIsC04?si=7cV16yhTbiYbrl-b\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/Cxb1FUIsC04?si=7cV16yhTbiYbrl-b\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>Testing at the Edges using Mocks - GLA Summit 2024</summary><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>During this session, the concept of mocks and test doubles is introduced. We discuss the <a href=\"https://lmock.astemes.com\">LMock toolkit</a>, which scripts the boilerplate code and provides an expressive API for writing mock-based unit tests. The session was very well received and a recording is available below.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/AvenQTc_GCc?si=lQB1BB8Nso5-AdlT\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/AvenQTc_GCc?si=lQB1BB8Nso5-AdlT\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>Code Hygiene in LabVIEW - CNRood Reconnect Helsinki 2023</summary><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The purpose of this presentation was to share sensible patterns and ideas to make LabVIEW code easier to read, reason about, and maintain. I discuss common pitfalls and sources of bugs, as well as better practices and sensible defaults. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Unfortunately this presentation was not recorded, please get in touch if you are interested in the content.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>Test Driving a CLD - GLA Summit 2022</summary><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this presentation, the theme of test driven development (TDD) is continued. I used TDD to solve a Certified LabVIEW Developer (CTD) exam, and this presentation is an analysis of the process and the design which emerged.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/n3axtsT4BdU?si=cvsA6Q6ASVhKoxVe\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/n3axtsT4BdU?si=cvsA6Q6ASVhKoxVe\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>Unit Testing From the Trenches - GDevCon #3 Amsterdam</summary><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Test Driven Development (TDD) is a discipline and a process which enables higher quality and productivity by using tests to drive software design. The LabVIEW community could benefit from TDD techniques, but there are challenges with hardware, user interfaces, and other IO devices. Today I use TDD whenever I develop software and I have leveraged it in various applications including production test systems, embedded RT systems, and an application framework. In this presentation I share my experiences and discuss how to test drive LabVIEW design, including hardware and other IO. I will also share examples of how the discipline of TDD has improved my design, while simultaneously providing a quick way of testing the system at any time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/6cfifZbhZsE?si=zJl1cH97DuA6fZWg\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/6cfifZbhZsE?si=zJl1cH97DuA6fZWg\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>Snake Game using Test Driven Development</summary><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In this 2 hour session we develop the classic game of Snake using test driven development. Unfortunately the sound is not very good in this recording.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://youtu.be/cgOtv9jrpvc?si=JJI5R0fY8M00OkF3\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://youtu.be/cgOtv9jrpvc?si=JJI5R0fY8M00OkF3\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:details -->\n<details class=\"wp-block-details\"><summary>LUnit Unit Test Framework - GLA Summit 2021</summary><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This presentation introduces the first released version of the open source <a href=\"https://lunit.astemes.com\">LUnit toolkit</a>. This presentation goes through the features of LUnit and discusses the concept of test inheritance.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:embed {\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kys_w2RNffw\\u0026t=1145s\\u0026ab_channel=GLASummit\",\"type\":\"video\",\"providerNameSlug\":\"youtube\",\"responsive\":true,\"className\":\"wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Kys_w2RNffw&amp;t=1145s&amp;ab_channel=GLASummit\n</div></figure>\n<!-- /wp:embed --></details>\n<!-- /wp:details -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Presentations', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '280-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-08-29 10:36:48', '2025-08-29 09:36:48', '', 280, 'https://www.astemes.com/staging/?p=291', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(293, 1, '2025-08-30 11:09:00', '2025-08-30 10:09:00', '<!-- wp:heading {\"className\":\"alignwide has-text-align-wide\",\"style\":{\"typography\":{\"lineHeight\":\"1.1\",\"fontSize\":\"90px\"}}} -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading alignwide has-text-align-wide\" style=\"font-size:90px;line-height:1.1\">Test and Measurement Solutions<p class=\"has-text-align-wide\"></p></h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns {\"align\":\"wide\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns alignwide\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Astemes is a solutions provider for test and measurement applications. We develop systems to automate testing of electro-mechanical products through the entire product life cycle. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We are your partner in test automation. From early proof-of-concepts and prototyping, through verification and validation, production testing, and beyond. We have high certified competency in the NI LabVIEW and NI TestStand software as well as extensive experience using and integrating various measurement devices and instruments. We are also effective working in text based languages such as Python, C++, C# and Java.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Software Development</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We develop high quality industrial software for test and measurement applications. We provide software development services based on your needs, working either as part of your team or independently. Because communication is at least as important as problem solving in software engineering, we prefer to work incrementally where we continuously deliver business value and gather feedback.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Turn-Key Solutions</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The best results are achieved when we get involved early on during requirement gathering and design specification. After this phase we lead the project and find the best components and subcontractors, to deliver according to the agreed upon schedule. We work hard to keep the customer involved through the whole project to validate our understanding and steer the project along the way.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column -->\n\n<!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":3} -->\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Training</h3>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We offer tailored training, presentations and workshops related to testing, process and software development. We either schedule the sessions over a shorter time period or define a cadence with sessions spread out over a longer period. The content may be delivered either on-site, remotely, or as a combination of the two. We also offer professional code reviews and pair programming.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We use industry standard technologies and proven frameworks to efficiently produce high quality software. By leveraging open source and proprietary software for common and generic tasks, we can focus on the core domain problems and avoid reinventing known solutions. This also reduces the maintenance cost and total cost of ownership over the lifecycle of the system.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->', 'Astemes', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-08-30 11:09:00', '2025-08-30 10:09:00', '', 16, 'https://www.astemes.com/staging/?p=293', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(295, 1, '2025-08-30 11:10:56', '2025-08-30 10:10:56', '', 'champ', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'champ', '', '', '2025-08-30 11:10:56', '2025-08-30 10:10:56', '', 150, 'http://www.astemes.com/staging/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/champ.png', 0, 'attachment', 'image/png', 0),
(296, 1, '2025-08-30 11:16:42', '2025-08-30 10:16:42', '<!-- wp:columns {\"align\":\"wide\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns alignwide\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Astemes provides expertise in design and development of automated test and measurement systems. Our mission is to enable innovation and excellence by providing world class technical expertise. We value software craftmanship and continuously work to improve and widen our offerings by actively participating in the international community. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We are an official <strong>NI (National Instruments) Partner</strong> and have high certified competency within the NI toolchain, including the <strong>Certified LabVIEW Architect (CLA)</strong> and <strong>Certified TestStand Developer (CTD)</strong> certifications. The CLA is the highest level of certification offered for <strong>NI LabVIEW</strong>. We are especially proud a bout the title as <strong>LabVIEW Champion</strong>, which is awarded to individuals as a recognition of <strong>deep technical expertise</strong> and valuable contributions to the <strong>community </strong>and <strong>ecosystem</strong>. We are also highly effective working in <strong>Python </strong>and comfortable with <strong>Java, C# </strong>and <strong>C++</strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>We value transparency and always deliver to the best of our ability. While we do want our customers to come back, we have no intention to lock anyone in. Source code and documentation is, for this reason, always provided as part of our deliveries.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Astemes is based in Pietarsaari, Finland.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->\n\n<!-- wp:gallery {\"linkTo\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-gallery has-nested-images columns-default is-cropped\"><!-- wp:image {\"id\":295,\"sizeSlug\":\"full\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img src=\"https://www.astemes.com/staging/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/champ.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-295\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":164,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.astemes.com/staging/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/CLA_2.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-164\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:image {\"id\":165,\"sizeSlug\":\"large\",\"linkDestination\":\"none\"} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img src=\"https://www.astemes.com/staging/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/CTD.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-165\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image --></figure>\n<!-- /wp:gallery -->\n\n<!-- wp:columns {\"align\":\"wide\"} -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-columns alignwide\"><!-- wp:column -->\n<div class=\"wp-block-column\"><!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\">About NI Partner Network&nbsp;</h4>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The NI Partner Network is&nbsp;a global community of&nbsp;domain, application, and overall test development&nbsp;experts&nbsp;working&nbsp;closely with NI to&nbsp;meet&nbsp;the needs of the engineering community.&nbsp;NI Partners are&nbsp;trusted solution providers, systems integrators, consultants, product developers,&nbsp;and&nbsp;services and sales channel partners&nbsp;skilled&nbsp;across&nbsp;a wide range of&nbsp;industries and application areas. Learn more&nbsp;and connect with the NI Partner Network at&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.ni.com/findapartner\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">ni.com/partners</a>.&nbsp;</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph --></div>\n<!-- /wp:column --></div>\n<!-- /wp:columns -->', 'About us', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '150-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-08-30 11:16:42', '2025-08-30 10:16:42', '', 150, 'https://www.astemes.com/staging/?p=296', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
